nodes.text: What's next?
Annot: What's next?
No, no, no!
JJMurray(365): No, no, no!
Annot: No, no, no!
If you have an allergy to peanuts and you know you have it then take your own precautions.
JJMurray(365): If you have an allergy to peanuts and you know you have it then take your own precautions.
Annot: If you have an allergy to peanuts and you know you have it then take your own precautions.

If I decide to bring a bag of peanuts onboard an airplane and am then told I'm in a "peanut free zone" or something like that, then my rights have been trampled as have the rights of everyone in that zone.

JJMurray(365): If I decide to bring a bag of peanuts onboard an airplane and am then told I'm in a "peanut free zone" or something like that, then my rights have been trampled as have the rights of everyone in that zone.

Annot: If I decide to bring a bag of peanuts onboard an airplane and am then told I'm in a "peanut free zone" or something like that, then my rights have been trampled as have the rights of everyone in that zone.
Request peanut free services from the airlines for yourself,
JJMurray(365): Request peanut free services from the airlines for yourself,
Annot: Request peanut free services from the airlines for yourself,
but do not force those restrictions on the rest of the flying public.
JJMurray(365): but do not force those restrictions on the rest of the flying public.
Annot: but do not force those restrictions on the rest of the flying public.
I have no problem with the airline offering peanut free foods, etc.
JJMurray(365): I have no problem with the airline offering peanut free foods, etc.
Annot: I have no problem with the airline offering peanut free foods, etc.
but it should be an option that people can select
JJMurray(365): but it should be an option that people can select
Annot: but it should be an option that people can select
not a requirement for everyone else to abide by.
JJMurray(365): not a requirement for everyone else to abide by.
Annot: not a requirement for everyone else to abide by.
JJMurray(365): What's next?
Can I have all perfume banned from an airplane or have people wearing them banned?
JJMurray(365): Can I have all perfume banned from an airplane or have people wearing them banned?
Annot: Can I have all perfume banned from an airplane or have people wearing them banned?
How about deodorants, hair sprays, any product with latex in it?
JJMurray(365): How about deodorants, hair sprays, any product with latex in it?
Annot: How about deodorants, hair sprays, any product with latex in it?
It is not a "right" if you have to impose that behavior on others for yourself.
JJMurray(365): It is not a "right" if you have to impose that behavior on others for yourself.
Annot: It is not a "right" if you have to impose that behavior on others for yourself.
What about my child's "right" not to die?
chartley81(389): What about my child's "right" not to die?
Annot: What about my child's "right" not to die?
I agree with chartley81.
ambersky(302): I agree with chartley81.
Annot: I agree with chartley81.
My child has a right to live.
ambersky(302): My child has a right to live.
Annot: My child has a right to live.
What about the fact that other things have been banned on airlines
ambersky(302): What about the fact that other things have been banned on airlines
Annot: What about the fact that other things have been banned on airlines
I think you can survive not eating peanuts for a few hours,
ambersky(302): I think you can survive not eating peanuts for a few hours,
Annot: I think you can survive not eating peanuts for a few hours,
but my son may not survive the flight if you decide to touch the armrest with a peanut oil covered hand and then he touches it.
ambersky(302): but my son may not survive the flight if you decide to touch the armrest with a peanut oil covered hand and then he touches it.
Annot: but my son may not survive the flight if you decide to touch the armrest with a peanut oil covered hand and then he touches it.
yes there are always risks
ambersky(302): yes there are always risks
Annot: yes there are always risks
but banning it lessens that risk to an extent.
ambersky(302): but banning it lessens that risk to an extent.
Annot: but banning it lessens that risk to an extent.
Where is your "right" to fly?
JJMurray(365): Where is your "right" to fly?
Annot: Where is your "right" to fly?
Or where is your "right" to limit my choices?
JJMurray(365): Or where is your "right" to limit my choices?
Annot: Or where is your "right" to limit my choices?
The shampoo ban is supposed to be to prevent liquid explosives from being brought onboard, not to prevent exposure to some allergic to it.
JJMurray(365): The shampoo ban is supposed to be to prevent liquid explosives from being brought onboard, not to prevent exposure to some allergic to it.
Annot: The shampoo ban is supposed to be to prevent liquid explosives from being brought onboard, not to prevent exposure to some allergic to it.
Sure I can "survive" without eating peanuts,
JJMurray(365): Sure I can "survive" without eating peanuts,
Annot: Sure I can "survive" without eating peanuts,
but you know what, you can also survive without flying wherever it is you are going,
JJMurray(365): but you know what, you can also survive without flying wherever it is you are going,
Annot: but you know what, you can also survive without flying wherever it is you are going,
why is it what you can survive is more important than what I can survive without?
JJMurray(365): why is it what you can survive is more important than what I can survive without?
Annot: why is it what you can survive is more important than what I can survive without?
What makes you more important than the 98% of the population that is not allergic to peanut products?
JJMurray(365): What makes you more important than the 98% of the population that is not allergic to peanut products?
Annot: What makes you more important than the 98% of the population that is not allergic to peanut products?
You have a responsibility to keep your child safe.
JJMurray(365): You have a responsibility to keep your child safe.
Annot: You have a responsibility to keep your child safe.
You don't let them play in traffic
JJMurray(365): You don't let them play in traffic
Annot: You don't let them play in traffic
but we don't ban cars.
JJMurray(365): but we don't ban cars.
Annot: but we don't ban cars.
This is no different.
JJMurray(365): This is no different.
Annot: This is no different.
It is YOUR responsibility,
JJMurray(365): It is YOUR responsibility,
Annot: It is YOUR responsibility,
it is not the airline's or the government's job to keep everything away from people that can hurt them
JJMurray(365): it is not the airline's or the government's job to keep everything away from people that can hurt them
Annot: it is not the airline's or the government's job to keep everything away from people that can hurt them
because you know what? Whatever you pick, someone out there has a SEVERE allergy to it that can kill them.
JJMurray(365): because you know what? Whatever you pick, someone out there has a SEVERE allergy to it that can kill them.
Annot: because you know what? Whatever you pick, someone out there has a SEVERE allergy to it that can kill them.
Pretty sure your kid will be fine.
howie(351): Pretty sure your kid will be fine.
Annot: Pretty sure your kid will be fine.
If not, DON'T FLY!!!
howie(351): If not, DON'T FLY!!!
Annot: If not, DON'T FLY!!!
I think the problem,
elizwestley(376): I think the problem,
Annot: I think the problem,
is that some people don't view peanuts in the same category as guns and cigarettes.
elizwestley(376): is that some people don't view peanuts in the same category as guns and cigarettes.
Annot: is that some people don't view peanuts in the same category as guns and cigarettes.
These things kill.
elizwestley(376): These things kill.
Annot: These things kill.
Just because they (peanuts) won't kill YOU doesn't make it your right to expose others to it.
elizwestley(376): Just because they (peanuts) won't kill YOU doesn't make it your right to expose others to it.
Annot: Just because they (peanuts) won't kill YOU doesn't make it your right to expose others to it.
It's a matter of education.
elizwestley(376): It's a matter of education.
Annot: It's a matter of education.
We'll get there.
elizwestley(376): We'll get there.
Annot: We'll get there.
This dialogue is a good step.
elizwestley(376): This dialogue is a good step.
Annot: This dialogue is a good step.
I don't support banning guns or cigarettes either.
JJMurray(365): I don't support banning guns or cigarettes either.
Annot: I don't support banning guns or cigarettes either.
Those are choices people make
JJMurray(365): Those are choices people make
Annot: Those are choices people make
and that is what I support and what I propose...choice.
JJMurray(365): and that is what I support and what I propose...choice.
Annot: and that is what I support and what I propose...choice.
If you think a ride is dangerous for your child you don't let them ride it.
JJMurray(365): If you think a ride is dangerous for your child you don't let them ride it.
Annot: If you think a ride is dangerous for your child you don't let them ride it.
Is it their "right" to be have the ride toned down for them or is it the right or every citizen to make a choice on what risk they accept and what they will not?
JJMurray(365): Is it their "right" to be have the ride toned down for them or is it the right or every citizen to make a choice on what risk they accept and what they will not?
Annot: Is it their "right" to be have the ride toned down for them or is it the right or every citizen to make a choice on what risk they accept and what they will not?
This, like many other regulations is simply taking that choice and handing it over to the government and forcing their decision on everyone.
JJMurray(365): This, like many other regulations is simply taking that choice and handing it over to the government and forcing their decision on everyone.
Annot: This, like many other regulations is simply taking that choice and handing it over to the government and forcing their decision on everyone.
Just because peanuts MAY kill someone doesn't mean everyone else should have no choice in eating them.
JJMurray(365): Just because peanuts MAY kill someone doesn't mean everyone else should have no choice in eating them.
Annot: Just because peanuts MAY kill someone doesn't mean everyone else should have no choice in eating them.
Unless you choke on them, these things (peanuts) WILL NOT kill anyone.
howie(351): Unless you choke on them, these things (peanuts) WILL NOT kill anyone.
Annot: Unless you choke on them, these things (peanuts) WILL NOT kill anyone.
Go to a real doctor and get tested  he will tell you peanuts are harmless.
howie(351): Go to a real doctor and get tested  he will tell you peanuts are harmless.
Annot: Go to a real doctor and get tested  he will tell you peanuts are harmless.
You are right on sir!
howie(351): You are right on sir!
Annot: You are right on sir!
Most of these supposed allergies are the paranoid imaginings of over anxious parents.
howie(351): Most of these supposed allergies are the paranoid imaginings of over anxious parents.
Annot: Most of these supposed allergies are the paranoid imaginings of over anxious parents.
The rest of the public should not be forced to accommodate them.
howie(351): The rest of the public should not be forced to accommodate them.
Annot: The rest of the public should not be forced to accommodate them.
A hive or two is not going to kill little jimmy, and the previous poster "shoeslut" should have her head examined for panicking like that.
howie(351): A hive or two is not going to kill little jimmy, and the previous poster "shoeslut" should have her head examined for panicking like that.
Annot: A hive or two is not going to kill little jimmy, and the previous poster "shoeslut" should have her head examined for panicking like that.
She is causing more harm to her child by being such a paranoid freak than any peanut ever will.
howie(351): She is causing more harm to her child by being such a paranoid freak than any peanut ever will.
Annot: She is causing more harm to her child by being such a paranoid freak than any peanut ever will.
